summary: Completed comprehensive testing of EventHive application. Backend APIs are fully functional (15/15 tests passed), admin functionality works perfectly, but identified critical frontend routing issue preventing users from accessing events page.

integration_issues.issue: Frontend routing not working properly - /events URL redirects to home page

passed_tests: Backend API - All 15 endpoints working (GET/POST/PUT/DELETE events, registrations, admin login)
Home page loads with welcome message and navigation
Admin can create new events successfully
Admin events table shows registration counts
Backend registration and duplicate prevention works

success_percentage.frontend: 60% - Home page and admin functionality work, but events page routing broken

action_item_for_main_agent: Fix frontend routing issue: /events URL is not loading the events page properly - it redirects to home page instead. This prevents users from viewing and registering for events. The backend API is working correctly and returns events data, but the frontend routing needs to be fixed.
